Reasoning: The paper deals with problems related to sorting permutations using a given set of allowed operations and computing the distance of the permutation. This is a fundamental problem in the study of genome rearrangements and interconnection networks, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses cycle graphs of permutations, which are a tool in Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses lower bounding edit distances, which is a problem in Symbolic Computation (cs.SC).
